QUIZ QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS - GENERAL SCIENCE

1) The human eye forms an image of an object at its:

(a) cornea

(b) iris

(c) pupil

(d) retina

Answer –

(d) retina


2) Name the sodium compound which is used for softening hard water?

(a) Sodium Carbonate

(b) Sodium Chloride

(c) Sodium Nitrate

(d) Sodium Sulphate

Answer-

(a) Sodium Carbonate


3) Name the acid present in Vinegar?

(a) Oxalic acid

(b) Acetic acid

(c) Citric acid

(d) NitriC acid

Answer-

(b) Acetic acid


4) Food cans are coated with tin and not with zinc because:

(a) Zinc is costlier than tin.

(b) Zinc has a higher melting point than tin.

(c) Zinc is more reactive than tin.

(d) Zinc is less reactive than tin.

Answer-

(c)  Zinc is more reactive than tin.


5) The human eye can focus objects at different distances by adjusting the focal length
   
   of the eye lens. This is due to:

(a) presbyopia

(b) accommodation

(c) near-sightedness

(d) far-sightedness

Answer-

(b) accommodation


6)A solution turns red litmus blue, its pH is likely to be:

(a) 1

(b) 4

(c) 5

(d) 10

Answer-

(d)10
 

7) The process of changing of water into its vapour is called:

(a) evaporation

(b) condensation

(c) sublimation

(d) precipitation

Answer –

(a) evaporation


8) The least distance of distinct vision for a young adult with normal vision is about:

(a) 25 m

(b) 2.5 cm

(c) 25 cm

(d) 2.5 m

Answer –

(c) 25 cm


9) If a plant has leaves with reticulate venation, what kind of roots will it have:

(a) fibrous root

(b) tap root

(c) adventitious root

(d) creeping root

Answer –

(b) Tap root


10) An element reacts with oxygen to give a compound with a high melting point.

    This compound is also soluble in water. The element is likely to be:

(a) Calcium

(b) Carbon

(c) Silicon

(d) Iron

Answer-

(a) Calcium


11) The change in focal length of an eye lens is caused by the action of the:

(a) pupil

(b) retina

(c) ciliary muscles

(d) iris

Answer-

(c) ciliary muscles


12) If a plant has fibrous root, what type of venation do its leaves have?

(a) pinnate venation

(b) reticulate venation

(c) palmate venation

(d) parallel venation

Answer-

(d)  parallel venation


13) Which of the following correctly describes the magnetic field near a long straight

    wire?

(a) The field consists of straight lines perpendicular to the wire.

(b) The field consists of straight lines parallel to the wire.

(c) The field consists of radial lines originating from the wire.

(d) The field consists of concentric circles centered on the wire.

Answer-

(d) The field consists of concentric circles centered on the wire.


14) Image formed by a plane mirror is:

(a) virtual, behind the mirror and enlarged.

(b) virtual, behind the mirror and of the same size as the object.

(c) real at the surface of the mirror and enlarged.

(d) real, behind the mirror and of the same size as the object.

Answer-

(b) virtual, behind the mirror and of the same size as the object.


15) The device used for producing electric current is called:

(a) electric generator

(b) galvanometer

(c) ammeter

(d) electric motor

Answer-

(a) electric generator


16) Name the process in which the passage of water goes from a region of higher
  
    concentration to a region of lower concentration through a semi permeable

	membrane?

(a) Diffusion

(b) Osmosis

(c) Both (a) and (b)

(d) Neither (a) nor (b)

Answer-

(b) Osmosis


17) The jelly like substance present inside the cell is known as:

(a) Cytoplasm

(b) Ectoplasm

(c) Nucleoplasm

(d) None of the above

Answer-

(a) Cytoplasm


18) Name the outer most boundary of the cell?

(a) Nuclear membrane

(b) Cytoplasm

(c) Plasma membrane

(d) None of the above

Answer-

(c) Plasma membrane


19) Night blindness is caused due to the deficiency of:

(a) Vitamin A

(b) Vitamin B

(c) Vitamin C

(d) Vitamin D

Answer-

(a) Vitamin A


20) A device that is used to break an electric circuit is called:

(a) bulb

(b) switch

(c) battery

(d) resistor

Answer-

(b) switch


21) In Mendeleev ’s Periodic Table, gaps were left for the elements to be discovered

    later. Which of the following elements found a place in the perioidc table later

(a) Germanium

(b) Chlorine

(c) Oxygen

(d) Silicon

Answer-

(a) Germanium


22) Water drops appear on the outer surface of a glass containing cold water. It is
   
    due to:

(a) evaporation

(b) precipitation

(c) transpiration

(d) condensation

Answer-

(d) condensation


23) Rickets is caused due to deficiency of:

(a) vitamin A

(b) vitamin B

(c) vitamin C

(d) vitamin D

Answer-

(d) Vitamin D
 
 
24) Which one of the following is a Natural fiber?

(a) nylon

(b) acrylic

(c) cotton

(d) polyester

Answer-

(c) cotton


25) Which organelle is known as the 'powerhouse of the cell'? 
   
(a) mitochondria

(b) nucleus

(c) cytoplasm

(d) ribosomes

Answer-

(a) mitochondria


26) What is the audible range of the average human ear?

(a) above 20,000 Hz

(b) 20 Hz to 20,000 Hz

(c) below 20 Hz

(d) 7.83 Hz

Answer-

(b) 20 Hz to 20,000 Hz


27) Who discovered cells?
    
(a) Marie Francois

(b) David Thomson

(c) Robert Hooke

(d) Robert Crook

Answer-

(c) Robert Hooke


28) In which kingdom will you place an organism which is single-celled, eukaryotic 
    
	and photosynthetic?
    
(a) Protista 

(b) Animalia

(c) Plantae

(d) Fungi

Answer-

(a) Protista 


29) Motion of the needle of a sewing machine is:

(a) translational motion

(b) rotational motion

(c) periodic motion

(d) non-periodic motion

Answer-

(c) periodic motion


30) What is the formulae of sodium oxide?
   
(a) NaCl

(b) Na2O

(c) Na2S

(d) Na2SO4

Answer-

(b)  Na2O
